observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE direct the MDRRMO:

a. To fast track the implementation of priority PPAs out of the DRRM funds;

b. Henceforth implement all LDRMM –PPAS as programmed in the AIP and LDRRMF Investment Plan in order to enhance the LGU’s pre-disaster preparedness and post-disaster response and recovery capability in times of calamities.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:

a.	The Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Development Coordinator to facilitate the fast-track implementation of the projects and programs funded out of the 20% DF, and henceforth, implement the identified PPAs as planned and scheduled;

b.	The Municipal Accountant to facilitate the submission of lacking supporting documents, and thus ensure the completeness of documents in support to payments made to contractors and other suppliers before billings are processed for payment.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require:

The designated employee and the Inventory Committee members to prioritize the conduct of physical count of the municipality’s road network system and submit a report thereon;

The Municipal Accountant to disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements additional necessary information on the agency’s Road Networks based on the reports that will be prepared and submitted.

We recommended that the LCE:

a. Advise the Municipal Treasurer to strictly require all the Revenue Collectors to turn-over daily and intact, all collections in accordance with Sections 26 and 33 of COA Circular No. 92-382;

b. Require the Liquidating Officer to verify the Report of Collections submitted by all accountable officers, count the money turned over to him, sign the certification and receipt portion;

c. Require the Municipal Treasurer to deposit intact all collections including the remittances of the Liquidating Officer.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

a. Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking documents on the use of 30% QRF and thus ensure the completeness of supporting documents before payment is made to suppliers;

b. Require the MSWDO, LDRRMO and other concerned offices to ensure that receipt and distribution of in-kind donations should always be supported with complete documentation for transparency and accountability.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE):

a. Require all drivers of motor vehicles to prepare and submit the Monthly Report of Official Travels for each motor vehicle;

b. Instruct the Supply Officer to require from each requisitioner of fuel and oil products an approved Requisition and Issuance Slip (RIS) and Driver’s Trip Ticket;

c. Direct the Supply Officer/personnel in-charge to serially number the Driver’s Trip Tickets issued, prepare Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption for each motor vehicle and submit on a monthly basis the said report to the auditor for audit/verification.

From the foregoing deficiencies, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the GAD Focal Person to:
Coordinate with other offices concerned in spearheading the implementation of GAD related activities;
Submit the documents required under Section 5.2 of the DBM-NEDA-NCRFW Joint Circular No. 2004-1 in support to the Annual GAD Accomplishment Report to facilitate validations of the accomplishments reported to determine compliance with the programs/projects/activities as provided for in the General Appropriation Act.

To correct the deficiencies, we recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the:

Municipal Engineer to retrieve all the Certificate of Turn-over and Final Acceptance, or Deed of Donation or any document that will establish the transfer and ownership of these assets to the barangay end-user;

Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting entries to reflect the correct balances of the affected accounts both in the LGU and Barangay books of accounts upon transfer ownership.

We recommended that the LCE:

a. Create an Appraisal and Disposal Committee to prepare the IIRUP and initiate the disposal of unserviceable properties in accordance with Section 79 of PD 1445 and COA Circular 92-386;

b. After the disposal, require the Disposal Committee to submit the necessary documents to the Accountant, as the basis of the latter to drop the unserviceable properties from the book of accounts in accordance with the existing accounting and auditing rules and regulations.

