13.6	We recommended that the LCE direct the MDRRMO:
To fast track the implementation of priority PPAs out of the DRRM funds;
Henceforth implement all DRRM – PPAS as programmed in the AIP and LDRRMF Investment Plan in order to enhance the LGU’s pre-disaster preparedness and post-disaster response and recovery capability in times of calamities.

14.6	We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:
The Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Development Coordinator to facilitate the fast-track implementation of the projects and programs funded out of the 20% DF, and henceforth, implement the identified PPAs as planned and scheduled;
The Municipal Accountant to facilitate the submission of lacking supporting documents, and thus ensure the completeness of documents in support to payments made to contractors and other suppliers before billings are processed for payment.

We recommended that the LCE require:
The Municipal Accountant to coordinate with the former OIC Municipal Accountant and verify previous records in order to identify the person/s accountable;
The former OIC Accountant to turnover all documents and records that will show the details of the undeposited collections including the name/s of person/s accountable, otherwise, institute appropriate disciplinary action against her for allowing the funds in the hands of the persons accountable  without the proper recording/reporting;
The person/s identified as accountable to immediately deposit the amount to the LGU’s depository bank.

We recommended that the LCE:
create an Inventory Committee that will be responsible in the conduct physical count on all Property, Plant and Equipment of the LGU including Local Road Networks;
render a complete and valid report thereon duly classified by type of PPE using the prescribed format of the report and;
reconcile the total value of each type of PPE with that of the accounting records, to ascertain the accuracy of the PPE accounts shown in the financial statements.

We recommended that management:
(a) Fast track the implementation of the PPAs consistent with Section 4.6 of COA Circular No. 94-013 and the MOAs for the benefit of the targeted constituents;
(b) Return to the Source Agency the balance of unutilized fund for completed projects in accordance with COA Circular No. 94-013 to enable the National government to re-appropriate the funds to other priority programs.

We recommended that management:
implement immediately the PPAs funded under the 20% DF for CY 2019;
henceforth implement within the timeline as scheduled in the AIP thru an  updated preparation of technical documents for the projects on the part of the Municipal Engineer’s Office, and effetive monitoring on the part of the MPDC, consistent with  the mandated responsibility of LGU officials, as embodied in the Joint DBM-DILG Memorandum Circular 2017-1.

We recommended that Local Chief Executive (LCE) require the LDRRMO:
a) To properly plan, prioritize and evaluate the programs, projects and activities under the four (4) Thematic areas to be funded out of the available LDRRM fund;
b) To submit the Report on Utilization of DRRM Funds, including the utilization of the Special Trust Fund, on a monthly basis using the prescribed format;
c) To ensure the optimum use of the fund by implementing the identified priority PPAs to attain the objective and purpose of the establishment of the DRRM funds.

We recommended that management:
Fast track the implementation of the PPAs consistent with the MOAs for the immediate use of the intended beneficiaries;
Return to the Source Agency the balance of unutilized fund for projects already completed in accordance with COA Circular No. 94-013.

We recommend that:

a) 	The LSB  prepare the Annual SEF Budget following the procedure set forth in the Joint Circular and furnish the Local Accountant, Local Treasurer and Local Budget  Officer a  copy of the budget;

b) 	The Local Accountant prepare the annual report on SEF Utilization  using the format prescribed in the Joint Circular;

c) 	Use the appropriate expense account in recording expenses charged to SEF. 

d) 	Cash Advance should be granted to a Special Disbursing Officer connected with the LGU having an administrative supervision of the Accountable Officer for internal control measure, instead of somebody from the school.

e) 	 LGU’s officials concerned comply with the requirement of adequate procurement planning in accordance with RA 9184 that will regulate the procurement activities and discourage reimbursement of expenses.

We recommend that the LCE require the GAD Focal Person:

a. 	To identify/propose PPAs in the LGUs budget that will promote gender-responsive governance and women empowerment pursuant to the Joint Circular 2004-01 and incorporate the same in the GAD Plan;  

b. 	Monitor its proper implementation;

c. 	Prepare an Accomplishment Report based on the plan.

1) Comply strictly with the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 on the granting, utilization, and liquidation of cash advances;

2)  Require the accountable officers to liquidate the overdue cash advances.  Invoke the provisions of law authorizing the withholding of salary of personnel who unjustifiably fails to settle his cash advances within the prescribed period; and

3)File appropriate legal action, if warranted to those who have failed to liquidate the overdue cash advances after exhausting appropriate means including 	 those who are no longer in the government service.
